Oral disc and Tentacles. Oral disc circular, furrowed, creamy in contracted specimens; translucent, mesenterial insertions visible as pale lines in expanded specimens (
Figure 5
). Oral disc diameter exceeds column diameter, especially in expansion. Mouth concave, same color as oral disc in contracted specimens; round, creamy white, and elevated in center of disc in expanded specimens. Actinopharynx well developed, occupying about 1 / 3 length of column, same color as mouth in both contracted and expanded preserved specimens.
